The quake was centered at a depth of about 30 kilometers -LRB- 18.6 miles -RRB- in the Solomon Sea , some 56 kilometers -LRB- 35 miles -RRB- north of Sohano , a town on the island of Bougainville .
It occurred at 7:35 p.m. -LRB- 1035 GMT -RRB- , the agency said .
There were some aftershocks reported in the region , an agency official said Thursday .
But he added there were no fears of tsunamis , seismic waves caused by undersea disturbances such as earthquakes or volcanic activity .
A magnitude 7.8 is considered capable of causing widespread damage in populated areas .
